Reasoning: The paper deals with adversarial attacks on machine learning models, specifically in the context of automated surveillance cameras and person detection. This falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of adversarial patches also involves aspects of computer security (cs.CR). Additionally, the approach involves generating these patches using machine learning techniques, which falls under artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the use of real-life scenarios and video footage involves aspects of multimedia (cs.MM).
